What is an array? 
    A data structure that can hold more than one value at a time
    An ordered series of elements of the same type
 
Arrays vs lists:
    Store data the same
    Arrays only take a sinlge data type; Lists take multiple data types

Creating arrays in Python:
    1) For integers
        Import array module:
          a) import array (without alias)
          b) import array as arr (with alias)
          c) from array import* (with *)
    2) For any other type
        array_name = []
        
Array functions:
    1) Finding the length
        len(array_name)
    2) Adding elements
        a) append() - Adds an element to the end
        b) extend() - Adds more than one element to the end
        c) insert() - Adds an element in a specific position
            insert(index_num,new_num)
    3) Removing elements
        a) pop() - removes an element at the end and returns it
        b) pop(index_value_you_want_removed) - removes a specific element and returns it
        b) remove(element_you_want_removed) - removes a specific element without returning it
